====Quotations====
* '''1667''': Rodolphus therefore finding such an earnest Invitation, embrac'd it with thanks, and with his Servant and Portmanteau, went to Don Juan's; where they first found good Stabling for their Horses, and afterwards as good Provision for themselves. &mdash; Charles Croke, ''Fortune's Uncertainty''
* '''1872''': Well, "slithy" means "lithe and slimy." "Lithe" is the same as "active." You see it's like a portmanteau &mdash; there are two meanings packed up into one word. &mdash; Lewis Carroll, ''Alice Through the Looking Glass''; the first usage of the word in this sense.

